CHILE DAYBOOK: Central Bank Economists’ Survey, Rate Decision

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-04-12T03:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/chile-daybook-central-bank-economists-survey-rate-decision.html
Chile ’s central bank will probably
raise its benchmark interest rate today for the tenth time in 11
months as surging economic growth sends inflation beyond the
mid-point of policy makers’ target.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*The five-member policy board, led by bank President Jose De Gregorio, will release its April interest-rate decision on the
bank’s website from 5 p.m. New York time.
*The central bank publishes a monthly survey of economists on
its website at 7:30 a.m. New York time.
*ING Wealth Management conference on Latin American investment
opportunities from 7 a.m. New York time.
*Factorline SA, Chile’s second-largest factoring company by
clients, sells as much as $105 million of inflation-linked
bonds, according to Larrain Vial SA.  EQUITIES:
*The Ipsa index fell 0.4 percent to 4,694.
*Empresas La Polar SA fell 2.3 percent to 2,677.4 pesos, the
steepest loss in more than two weeks. Guillermo Luksic, chairman
of Quinenco SA, told reporters April 8 that he’s not interested
in buying a stake in the department store operator.
*Parque Arauco SA fell 1 percent to 1,071.60. Ollanta Humala, a
one-time ally of Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez , won the first
round of voting in  Peru ’s national election, according to a
preliminary count, and will face Keiko Fujimori in a second
round. Parque Arauco operates shopping centers in Peru.  MARKETS:
*Chile’s peso weakened 0.4 percent to 472.01 per  U.S. dollar 
from 469.91 on April 8.
*The central bank bought $50 million at an average of 470.44
pesos per dollar yesterday. The bank has been buying $50 million
a day since Jan. 5 as part of a plan to weaken the currency.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
